    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="62"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/4161</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-07T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5266. Your 6830, July 24, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d62fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_911">p. 911</ref>.</note>
                    Until Trading with the Enemy Act, now pending in Congress, is passed, this
                    Government cannot act in this matter. Under this act, as drafted and introduced
                    in Congress, definition of an enemy alien, with a few exceptions, is governed by
                    domicile and not by nationality. Impossible to tell at present date what form
                    final act will take.</p>
                <p>Since April 2 banks in New York have voluntarily reported all foreign exchange
                    transactions and often have, of their own initiative, refused to take
                    questionable business.</p>
                <p>Federal Reserve Board has sent a warning to all banks under its jurisdiction and
                    an appeal to those banks which are not under its jurisdiction to scrutinize
                    carefully all foreign business.<note n="2" xml:id="d62fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_814">p. 814</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0165" n="919" xml:id="pg_919"/>
                <p>Cable censor refuses to pass suspicious financial cables.</p>
                <p>Until Trading with the Enemy Act passes nothing further can be done in this
                    direction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
